cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.LO. 

The paper discusses a framework for modeling reconfigurable dynamic systems, which involves aspects of software engineering (cs.SE) such as coordination and creation/deletion of components, distributed computing (cs.DC) due to the mobility aspect, programming languages (cs.PL) due to the rule-based language used, systems and control (cs.SY) due to the need for endogenous/modular and exogenous/centralized coordination styles, and logic in computer science (cs.LO) due to the use of Interaction Logic as inspiration for the rule-based language.
